    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(center)"><placeName>San Francisco</placeName>
                <date>Jany 25th 1864—5624</date>.</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">My dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">I hope ere this reaches you, you will have<lb/> received the
                    mss<add>?</add> of the “Reflections on <add>לא תשבעו בשמי לשקר</add>” &amp;c and
                that<lb/> it will suit your Journal. I now send you the balance of the said
                article—<lb/> I hope by this time you will have quite recovered from you
                indisposition. I sent<lb/> you by last mail a pamphlet of the History of the Polish
                Jews which I translated<lb/> from the French. I should hope you have received it. I
                must observe to you<lb/> that should my articles not suit you, please return the
                    mss<add>?</add> as I have no copy<lb/> I do not mind the Postage I will return
                the amt of stamps required—but I hope<lb/> you will find my work acceptable and if
                so I will from time to time employ<lb/> my leisure hours to write for your Occident
                for I consider that to be the best<lb/> Jewish magazine in the whole
                    <placeName>United States</placeName> without any flattery, I read it at<lb/> all
                times with pleasure. I take opportunity to mention that I shall so on remit<lb/> you
                some money, my <sic>Income</sic> is very limited and every thing is very high in<lb/>
                <placeName>California</placeName> which keeps me poor, but never mind, <hi
                    rend="underline">better late than never</hi><lb/> I will shortly send you some
                statistics of <placeName>San Francisco</placeName> Jewish matters—at present<lb/>
                all is still. Some short time ago <persName>Mr de Solla</persName> formerly of
                    <placeName>Jamaica</placeName> wrote<lb/> some articles for the “Hebrew” on
                Angels &amp; Devils, I suppose you have read them<lb/> I have commenced a critique
                on the subject, I will finish it and send it to<lb/> you if you like to publish it
                in the occident. <sic>let</sic> me hear from you in return<lb/> Praying for your
                improved health</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">Believe me yours truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(11)">
                <persName role="author">H. A. Henry</persName>
            </p>
            <p>PS.</p>
            <p>You must not scold me for writing on</p>
            <p>both sides of the paper, I know it is not</p>
            <p>so good for the composition, but I do it to save postage. Still if you do not like
                it, I</p>
            <p>will do otherwise in future. <persName role="author">H. A. Hy</persName></p>
        </body>
